===Etymology===
From [[barefaced]] Bold or brazen; [[lie]] Falsehood

===Noun===
'''[[barefaced]] [[lie]]''' (''Plural:'' '''barefaced lies''')

# A [[falsehood]] told with utter [[confidence]], especially a [[planned]] or [[deliberate]] falsehood.
#:''I understand that salespeople try to explain things in a positive way, but that was a '''barefaced lie'''.''

